title: GHS Volleyball: Silver Streaks sweep Rocks
text: Posted Oct. 8, 2015 at 10:33 PM Posted Oct. 8, 2015 at 10:33 PM GALESBURG — Kaylah Townsell hammered a match best 14 kills to lead the Galesburg High School volleyball team to a 25-21, 25-20 sweep of Rock Island on Thursday. Shayli Florine add seven kills, Hailey Steveson made five digs and Brittnee Williams had five digs and two blocks for the Silver Streaks (13-9, 3-4). Kylee Townsell gave out 22 assists and served a pair of aces also for Galesburg. The Streaks’ sophomore team (18-2, 6-1) needed overtime in match two to pull off a 25-16, 28-26 win over the Rocks. Serena Bolden was tough at the net with 14 kills. Yvonne Mixon added seven kills and three blocks, Makailee Brown had three digs, Megan Lingafelter served two aces Sam Rogers gave out 13 assists for Galesburg. The Streaks’ freshmen team (9-7) fell to Rock Island 25-16, 25-18. Daija Range had seven kills and six blocks to lead Galesburg. Chloe McCarthy served 11 points and had three kills and Kesli Legge gave out five assists for the Streaks. The Register-Mail
